values:
First let me say how cool it is to use a computer that has the upside-down exclamation mark on it! It makes life so much easier:)

Sorry I haven't updated in awhile. I've been a little busy in the afternoons this past week. Last weekend we went to Manuel Antonio, one of the most beautiful beaches in Costa Rica. I don't have a lot of time right now, but I still am going to write an entry about that soon, so be looking for that! I also have a lot of pictures to put up online, including some from Arenal Volcano the weekend before. It takes FOREVER to upload pictures here, so I get frustrated after a few hours cause I'm tired of sitting by the computer. SO bear with me and keep checking, cause they will be up there soon! I've already put up some from Arenal, so if you haven't seen them yet go look cause it's gorgeous there. 

Today we leave for Monteverde, a cloud forest here. I'm going to do a canopy tour tomorrow, which is basically a zipline through the rainforest, moving from tree to tree, so expect lots of beautiful pictures!!

Well I hope everyone is doing well. I promise I'll write more next week (this week was also kind of busy because it was the last week of the first 3-week block. Next week I start Advanced Spanish Grammar, and the beginning of block is always the easiest.)

I miss and love all of you!

Hasta Luego,

Emily:)
